  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm baseline build passes; task 020 merged or branch-loadable; `IToolHandlerRegistry` interface available (created in task 014 module skeleton; task 026 fills in dispatch logic).</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay attention to spec.md FR-12 and design.md Â§7.4.1 worked example (full dispatch flow with parameter resolution + gate behavior).</step>
    <step order="2">Sketch `ResourceExecutionResult` response shape: `Status` enum (`Succeeded | GatePending | Failed`), `Payload` (the Tool's result on success; `JsonElement` or typed), `GateId` (when GatePending), `GateType`, `Error` (when Failed), `LatencyMs`, `AuditId`. Document defaults.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement `InvokeResourceTool.cs`: `[KernelFunction, Description("Invoke a Tool Registry resource. If the resource requires human approval (humanGate.required=true), returns GatePending status with a gateId. Otherwise executes immediately and returns the result.")]` `Task&lt;ResourceExecutionResult&gt; InvokeResourceAsync(string resourceId, Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt; parameters)`. Inject `IToolHandlerRegistry`, `IGateResolver?` (nullable), Dataverse client, `ICallerContext`.</step>
    <step order="4">Lookup the ToolRegistry entry by `resourceId`. Not-found â†’ return `ResourceExecutionResult.Failed { ErrorKind=NotFound }`. Caller without invoke permission â†’ return `Failed { ErrorKind=Forbidden }`.</step>
    <step order="5">Validate `parameters` against the Tool's parameter schema. Missing required â†’ return `Failed { ErrorKind=ValidationError, Detail="Missing required parameter: X" }`. Use JSON Schema validation.</step>
    <step order="6">Branch on `humanGate.required`:
      - **false**: call `IToolHandlerRegistry.DispatchAsync(resourceId, parameters)`. Catch `PhaseToolDeniedException` (task 026) â†’ return `Failed { ErrorKind=PhaseDenied }`. Catch generic exceptions â†’ `Failed { ErrorKind=ExecutionError }`. On success return `Succeeded { Payload, LatencyMs }`.
      - **true**: if `IGateResolver` is null (Phase 2 standalone), record gate-intent placeholder + return `GatePending { GateId=Guid.NewGuid().ToString(), GateType=humanGate.Type }`. If `IGateResolver` present (Phase 3+), call resolver to initiate gate flow and return `GatePending` with real gateId.</step>
    <step order="7">Emit App Insights metric `action_engine.metatool.latency` with dimension `metatool=invokeResource` and `outcome={succeeded|gatePending|failed}`. Tier 2 + Tier 3 audit via existing middleware.</step>
    <step order="8">Write unit tests: (a) direct execution happy path (no gate), (b) gate-pending path (humanGate.required = true, no resolver wired â€” returns placeholder), (c) gate-pending path (humanGate.required = true, mocked resolver â€” returns real gateId), (d) parameter validation rejects missing-required, (e) PhaseToolDeniedException â†’ Failed { ErrorKind=PhaseDenied }, (f) caller without invoke permission â†’ Forbidden, (g) not-found â†’ NotFound.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify build + tests + format: `dotnet build`, `dotnet test --filter "InvokeResource"`, `dotnet format`. Verify NFR-10 (no new packages).</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on `InvokeResourceTool.cs`; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (invoke permission checked), ADR-010 (DI), ADR-013 (NOT exposed via PublicContracts), ADR-015 (audit auto-applies), ADR-019 (ProblemDetails-shaped errors), ADR-029 (no new packages).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 024 âś…. Update `current-task.md`. Note the `IGateResolver?` nullable seam for Phase 3 awareness.</step>
    <step order="11">Document deviations in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Commit with brief recap.</step>
  </steps>

