  <notes>
    The `IGateResolver?` nullable seam is the critical Phase 2 / Phase 3 boundary. Tests in this task validate both states (null = Phase 2 standalone; non-null = Phase 3 wired). Phase 3 task 030 will wire the actual resolver implementations.

    JSON Schema validation library choice matters for NFR-10. Use a library already transitively present (`Json.More.Net` or similar already in BFF). If none is present, escalate â€” DO NOT silently add a new package.

    Audit middleware (ADR-015) handles Tier 2 + Tier 3 writes automatically on dispatch. The gate-pending path does NOT go through dispatch, so this task must explicitly log the gate-intent invocation to ensure full audit coverage (an `IAuditEvent` write or equivalent). Consult `AuditEnrichmentMiddleware` for the canonical write pattern.

    Direct invocation latency budget: not formally NFR-bound but should align with general AI-tool dispatch &lt;500ms p95. Measure in unit tests with stubbed handlers; load test in task 064 covers the registry-discovery path which is the SLO-bound one (NFR-01).
  </notes>

